  Volume                   = {9},

  Abstract                 = {A general introduction to person-fit research is given. Several types of aberrant response behavior on a test are discussed, and the issue of whether person-fit statistics can be used to detect such deviant score patterns is investigated. The role of examinee test-taking error (such as skipping a question, and then forgetting to skip a space on the answer sheet), and the possibility that deviant scores are the result of the particular characteristics of personality or other tests are also discussed in terms of item response theory. (PsycINFO Database Record (c) 2012 APA, all rights reserved)},
